 also works when i want to render it - to another Scene with Rendertarget\nsceneRTT.add(blendMesh);\n\nbut when i want to render the same blendmesh object to two scenes \n                scene.add( blendMesh );\n                sceneRTT.add(blendMesh);\nthen only one gets rendered...\n\nI think the problem is Rendering two times the same animated blendmesh.\n\nI can push anyother Threeobject to different renders and it works. But with that blendmesh i didnt get it.\n\nWould be super nice if you guys could help me out. I think it offers a lot of possiblities. Not sure - about defered - but wouldnt this also be needed?\n","created_at":"2015-12-20T23:03:41.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7494#issuecomment-166162013","id":166162013,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7494","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjE2MjAxMw==","updated_at":"2015-12-20T23:04:56.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166162013","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1371546?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/princemio","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNzE1NDY=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"princemio","type":"User","id":1371546,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/princemio\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I guess you only have one `AnimationMixer` that is updated once per frame, so there should be no problem on the animation side.\n\nPerhaps you have to force a matrix update? If that won't do, it's probably a renderer issue and you'll have to use two objects for now (see `AnimationObjectGroup` on `dev` to apply the same animation state to multiple objects).\n","created_at":"2015-12-23T11:52:49.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7494#issuecomment-166872268","id":166872268,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7494","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2Njg3MjI2OA==","updated_at":"2015-12-23T11:52:49.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166872268","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3916357?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/tschw","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM5MTYzNTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"tschw","type":"User","id":3916357,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Hey @tschw  - thank you man for looking into it. \n\nIn my description of the problem - i used the example http:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/webgl_animation_skinning_blending.html\nSo it 